Claims CLAIMS: 1. A prismatic battery cell system, comprising: two positive electrode tabs on a first side of the cell system and two negative electrode tabs on a second, negative side of the cell system, wherein the two positive electrode tabs are laterally offset from one another and wherein the two negative electrode tabs are laterally offset from one another. 2. The system of claim 1, further comprising a plurality of electrode pairs, each electrode pair in the plurality of electrode pairs including a positive electrode with a positive tab terminal and a negative electrode with a negative tab terminal. 3. The system of claim 2, wherein the positive tab terminal and the negative tab terminal are positioned at longitudinally opposite sides of each electrode pair. 4. The system of claim 2, wherein the plurality of electrode pairs are divided into a first group of electrode pairs and a second group of electrode pairs, and tabs terminals of the positive electrodes in the first group of electrode pairs are coupled to a first positive electrode tab of the two positive electrode tabs and tab terminals of the negative electrodes in the first group of electrodes pairs are coupled to a first negative electrode tab of the two negative electrode tabs. 5. The system of claim 4, wherein the tab terminals of the positive electrodes in the second group of electrodes pairs are coupled to a second positive electrode tab of the two positive electrode tabs and the tab terminals of the negative electrodes in the second group of electrodes pairs are coupled to a second negative electrode tab of the two negative electrode tabs. 6. The system of claim 5, wherein the each of the tabs terminals of the positive electrodes in the first group of electrode pairs, the tab terminals of the negative electrodes in the first group of electrodes pairs, the tab terminals of the positive electrodes in the second group of electrodes pair, and the tab terminals of the negative electrodes in the second group of electrodes are coupled to respective electrode tabs by ultrasonic consolidation welding. 7. A system for a battery cell, comprising: a first group of positive electrodes coupled to a first electrode tab; 

 a second group of positive electrodes coupled to a second electrode tab; a first group of negative electrodes coupled to a third electrode tab; and a second group of negative electrodes coupled to a fourth electrode tab, wherein each of the first electrode tab and the second electrode tab are arranged on a first side of the battery cell, and each of the third electrode tab and the fourth electrode tab are coupled to a second, opposite side of the battery cell. 8. The system of claim 7, wherein the first electrode tab is laterally offset from the second electrode tab, and wherein the third electrode tab is laterally offset from the fourth electrode tab. 9. The system of claim 7, wherein each electrode in each of the first group of positive electrodes, the second group of positive electrodes, the third group of negative electrodes, and the fourth group of negative electrodes includes a distinct uncoated tab terminal. 10. The system of claim 9, wherein each electrode in the battery cell system is a same size, such that upon stacking each electrode in the battery cell system, anode edges overhang cathode edges, except for each tab terminal. 11. The system of claim 10, wherein, upon stacking each electrode in the battery cell system, tab terminals of each electrode in the first group of positive electrodes align with the first electrode tab, tab terminals of each electrode in the second group of positive electrodes align with the second electrode tab, tab terminals of each electrode in the first group of negative electrodes align with the third electrode tab, and tab terminals of each electrode in the second group of negative electrodes align with the fourth electrode tab. 12. The system of claim 9, wherein tab terminals of each electrode in each of the first group of positive electrodes and the second group of positive electrodes are positioned along a first side of the cell, the tab terminals of each electrode in the first group of positive electrodes being laterally offset from the tab terminals of each electrode in the second group of positive electrodes. 13. The system of claim 12, wherein the tab terminals of each electrode in each of the first group of negative electrodes and the second group of negative electrodes are positioned along 

 a second side of the cell, and wherein the tab terminals of each electrode in the first group of negative electrodes being laterally offset from the tab terminals of each electrode in the second group of negative electrodes, the first side of the cell opposite to the second side of the cell. 14. The system of claim 9, wherein the tab terminal of each electrode in the first group of positive electrodes are welded to the first electrode tab, wherein the tab terminals of each electrode in the second group of positive electrodes are welded to the second electrode tab, wherein the tab terminals of each electrode in the first group of negative electrodes are welded to the third electrode tab, and wherein the tab terminals of each electrode in the second group of negative electrodes are welded to the fourth electrode tab. 15. The system of claim 1, wherein the first group of positive electrodes and the first group of negative electrodes each include an equal non-zero number of distinct electrodes, and wherein the second group of positive electrodes and the second group of negative electrodes include an equal non-zero number of distinct electrodes. 16. A battery module system, comprising: a plurality of cells, each cell including two positive electrode tabs and two negative electrode tabs; a first set of busbars coupling two consecutive cells of the plurality of cells on a first side of the module; a second set of busbars coupling two consecutive cells of the plurality of cells on a second side of the module; and a pair of adjacent positive terminals coupled to a positive end plate and a pair of adjacent negative terminals coupled to a negative end plate, wherein the plurality of cells are stacked in series between the positive end plate and the negative end plate. 17. The system of claim 16, wherein each of the first set of busbars and the second set of busbars include a plurality of cell to cell busbars, and wherein the first side of the module is opposite to the second side of the module. 18. The system of claim 16, wherein coupling two consecutive cells includes connecting a positive tab of a first cell to a negative tab of an immediately subsequent cell via a cell to cell busbar. 19. The system of claim 16, wherein the battery module includes an even number of cells, and wherein the positive terminals and the negative terminals are aligned along a third side of the module, wherein each positive terminal in the pair of positive terminals is mutually connected by a first lob and coupled to a first busbar which connects the module within a battery pack, and wherein each negative terminal in the pair of negative terminals is mutually connected by a second lob and coupled to a second busbar which connects the module within the battery pack. 20. The system of claim 19, wherein the battery module includes an odd number of cells, and wherein the positive terminals are aligned along the third side of the module while the negative terminals are aligned along a fourth side of the module, the third side opposite to the fourth side.
